ğŸ“š BookStore API

A full-stack Book Management System built with Node.js, Express, MongoDB, and React.
This app allows you to create, read, update, and delete books through a modern UI or RESTful API.

ğŸ§° Features

CRUD operations for books: create, read, update, delete

Responsive modern UI with Tailwind CSS (light & dark mode support)

Form validation and error handling

API endpoints secured with proper status codes and messages

Loading indicators and snackbars for smooth UX

âš¡ Tech Stack

Backend: Node.js, Express, Mongoose (MongoDB)

Frontend: React, Tailwind CSS, Axios, React Router

State Management: React useState, useEffect

Notifications: notistack

Dev Tools: Nodemon, Axios, dotenv, CORS

Frontend: http://localhost:3000

Backend: http://localhost:5000/api/books

ğŸ›  API Endpoints
Method	Endpoint	Description
GET	/api/books	Get all books
POST	/api/books	Create a new book
GET	/api/books/:id	Get a single book
PUT	/api/books/:id	Update a book
DELETE	/api/books/:id	Delete a book
ğŸ¨ Frontend Pages

Home: List all books (table/card view toggle)

Create Book: Add a new book with title, author, and publish year

Edit Book: Update book information

Show Book: View details of a book

Delete Book: Confirm and delete a book

All pages include dark mode, loading indicators, and snackbar notifications.

ğŸ›¡ Error Handling

Custom error class AppError

Global error handler in Express

Front-end notifications using notistack

ğŸ“Œ Notes

Make sure your MongoDB connection string is correct.

Ports should match in frontend and backend requests (5000 in backend, 3000 in frontend).

You can customize the dark mode theme in Tailwind config.

